Surplus production vs. biomass plot. For interpretation, see
Walters, Hilborn, and Christensen, 2008, Surplus production dynamics in declining and recovering fish populations. Can. J. Fish. Aquat. Sci. 65: 2536-2551.
Data presence by year for each fleet and data type.

Data presence by year for each fleet, where circle area is
relative within a data type. Circles are proportional to
total catch for catches; to precision for indices, discards, and
mean body weight observations; and to total sample size for
compositions and mean weight- or length-at-age observations.
'Ghost' observations (not included in the likelihood) have
equal size for all years.
Note that since the circles are are scaled relative
to maximum within each type, the scaling within separate plots
should not be compared.

Parameter distribution plots (plot 1 of 4).
Deviation parameters are not included.
Plotting range is equal to input limits on parameters. Use fitrange = TRUE to scale the range to the estimates.

Table of estimated parameters (excluding deviation parameters) sorted by parameters with the largest gradients; any parameter with a gradient value with an absolute value above 0.001 (for SS 3.30 models) or a parameter on bounds is colored in red.
